#depression
1. Enjoy the moments... because they pass by quickly 

2. Adopt an attitude of gratitude. Has great healing potential 

3. Do not isolate yourself , build a network and communicate. Makes you not feel lonely 

4. Immerse yourself in work , it starves your distractions

Sadly, we don’t always know the depths of someone’s depression until it is too late. 🥺 May I please have even 1 friend to copy and re-post? I am trying to demonstrate that someone is listening.        
                           Just one.

If you, or a loved one is suicidal, PLEASE know there IS help available! Please know that sometimes it takes a few tries to find the right person to help you.

It’s NOT easy to ride the roller coaster called life, but it’s worth it, because YOU are worth it!
~HUGS~

media.altText:
An orange background with a Rethink Mental Illness logo at the bottom. 

At the top, there are the words "3 out of 4" in big letters, with an illustration of four people below it, three coloured in blue and the other left blank.

Words on the right say 76% of people living with mental illness say their anxiety has prevented them from seeing their friends and family.

An orange background with a Rethink Mental Illness logo at the bottom. 

At the top, there are the words "3 out of 4" in big letters, with an illustration off four people below it, three coloured in blue and the other left blank.

Words on the right say 74% of people living with mental illness say their anxiety has prevented them from taking part in exercise of hobbies.

An orange background with a Rethink Mental Illness logo at the bottom. 

At the top, there is a big 65% with an illustration of a battered old sofa below it.

Words on the right read: "65% of people living with mental illness say their anxiety has prevented them from leaving the house"

An orange background with a Rethink Mental Illness logo at the bottom. 

At the top, there is a big 60% with an illustration of a briefcase below it.

Words on the right read: "60% of people living with mental illness say their anxiety has prevented them from going to work/education/volunteering"

media.altText:
Plain white background with black text, which reads:

'You have to learn to see everything.
Not just look at it.
Textures,
Like the crispness of leaves
And the softness of silk.

Observe the fragility of the spider's web,
Precariously hanging
By finely woven thread.

Are we not just living the same way
Hanging on,
Day by day,
And waiting to fall?

But nature's colours,
Made vibrant by rain,
Has made me want
To live again'.

Als Psychosozialer Berater des Bundesverbandes Burnout und #Depression (@BBuD2013) habe ich mich dafür eingesetzt, dass wir die Arbeitszeiten in Deutschland flexibilisieren. Das bedeutet aber nicht, dass in jedem Beruf die #VierTageWoche gelten soll. Stattdessen braucht es - wie beim Renteneintritt - atmende Lösungen, die individuell verschieden sind und sich von starren, allgemeinen Vorgaben lösen. 

Grundsätzlich muss aber Menschen, die gerade in körperlich wie psychisch herausfordernden Jobs arbeiten und dort aufgrund von potenzieller Überlastung der Gefahr von möglichen dauerhaften #Gesundheitsschäden ausgesetzt sind, die Chance und Option gegeben werden, entsprechend der jeweiligen Kräfte und der #Leistungsfähigkeit gleitende Modelle in Anspruch nehmen zu können.

Das bedeutet aber nicht, dass in jedem Beruf die #VierTageWoche gelten soll. Stattdessen braucht es - wie beim Renteneintritt - atmende Lösungen, die individuell verschieden sind und sich von starren, allgemeinen Vorgaben lösen. 

Grundsätzlich muss aber Menschen, die gerade in körperlich wie psychisch herausfordernden Jobs arbeiten und dort aufgrund von potenzieller Überlastung der Gefahr von möglichen dauerhaften #Gesundheitsschäden ausgesetzt sind, die Chance und Option gegeben werden, entsprechend der jeweiligen Kräfte und der #Leistungsfähigkeit gleitende Modelle in Anspruch nehmen zu können.
